{
  "texts": [
    "Besides the basic information ( e.g.",
    "gender, region, highest_education) of students, Table 1 summarizes online learning activities to construct dynamic graphs.Baselines The case study employs a variety of machine learning models as baselines to evaluate our proposed APP-TGN.",
    "They are -optimized multiple layer perception (OMLP) [69], ProbSAP [70], CNN-LSTM [71], graph neural networks MTGNN [18] and a modified multi-view graph transformer from [31] (noted as AP-GT), hybrid recurrent networks (HRNs) [72] and a variant of our model, denoted APP-TGN1, where APP-TGN Fig. 2 Statistics of code-Module FFF in OULA substitutes the TGN module for TGN as per [73].",
    "This variant serves the role of baseline models, and we contrast it against our newly introduced APP-TGN.",
    "Both the reference models and our APP-TGN are built using PyTorch and Python."
  ]
}